  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging docs: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Monitor/Logging/ -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nNoticed during a full sync of goerli using `--Xbonsai-use-snapshots=true`, off-heap memory grows substantially.  Taking a heap dump it is clear that the TransactionPool is inadvertently keeping a reference to the worldstate used to validate transactions as well as track recent sender invalid nonces.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"961\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-11-04 at 8 57 49 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1238512/200099838-e6713310-ddfe-428a-b95a-ed5ae2fb2560.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* ensure TransactionPool does not keep references to worldstate or transactions\r\n* do not overconsume off-heap memory \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. on a node with bonsai snapshots enabled, start a full sync of the chain\r\n2. observe off-heap memory consumption during the full sync\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nSnapshot transactions are closed and off-heap memory is freed as the chain progresses\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nTransaction Pool keeps references to as many as 10k snapshot transactions, consuming significant off-heap memory\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\n100%\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: 22.10.0\r\n",
